### Custom Augmented Spark Igniter For Liquid Propellant Rocket Engine

Technologies and skills used: Autodesk Fusion, NASA CEA, ANSYS Mechanical, ANSYS Fluent, Lathe & Mill

I am designing an augmented spark igniter (ASI), a miniature rocket engine used to ignite a larger rocket engine using liquid bipropellants. The ASI needs to ignite a pressure-fed liquid bipropellant engine operating at a chamber pressure of 600 psi. This is a high pressure environment, which is a more challenging situation for designing this ASI.

Problem Statement: Design a liquid bipropellant ASI capable of producing a high temperature and reliable flame into a 600 psi rocket engine chamber. 

Conditions & Constraints:
- Thrust: 10 N
- O/F Ratio: 2
- Temperature of flame produced: >900 K
- This value is above the autoignition temperature for the combination of fuel and oxidizer
- Fuel: Ethanol
- Oxidizer: Nitrous Oxide
- Exit Environment Pressure: 600 psi
- Maximum dimensions: 5” x 5” x 6”
- Material: AISI 1018 steel
- Able to be machined with standard lathe and mill and assembled with basic tools



